reviews.text: Comprehensive display of Lake Wales and Polk County. My family and I enjoyed our visit. I plan to return when I have time to scrutinize the information presented in the exhibits. It is located next to the historic downtown district.
The history of Lake Wales, Florida kept alive here to educate future generations. Highly recommended 👍👍.
Very interesting and well run! A good place to go on a rainy day.
Great place.
Fantastic place. Glad to see that something in Lake Wales is so well run.
Loved it. The trails are clearly marked and well kept. The lady at the front gate was very nice and knowledgeable. I knew right off we were in a good place. For once the map was pretty accurate.

A beautiful and interesting Florida state park located in Lake Wales, FL. Large crushed shell sites were very level. Gorgeous live oak trees draped with moss gives an exotic feel to the campground. Clean, modern bathhouse. My favorite part was the Cow Camp, an historically accurate pioneer camp with an interpretive guide on weekends. A must see. This is a large, paved park so bring your bikes and golf carts. Its no actually on Lake Kissimmee so check for public boat launches.

Good trails. Clean bathrooms. A good bit of distance available to cover and the trails are fairly shaded for several miles which is nice in the hotter months. It was not quite as scenic as I hoped though.
One of my favorite parks in Florida. Very well kept. Has a camping area and a small store with the basics. You can also rent kayaks and canoes :)

Our first trip in our new camper, and what a wonderful experience! Such a great time with my wife, and the dogs loved it too. The camping loops at Lake Kissimmee are in a dense hammock, and most sites seem to offer privacy. Nice, clean facilities, and plenty of wildlife (we saw armadillos, a possum, a large turtle, and dozens of hawks). Jerome the Armadillo seemed particularly fond of our campsite, wandering through numerous times during our three nights in the wild.
It was nice the owner let me lick peanut butter off his toes
Love this place!
One of my favorite little get aways, nice little spot.

A nice Polk County Environmental Area along wild Walk-in-Water Creek.  There are, as of this time, December 2016, only a few short trails and a small fishing lake.  The tropical oak hammock is extremely beautiful with live oaks covered with wild orchids, bromeliads and resurrection fern.  You can easily miss the entrance since the new pipeline construction is blocking it's entrance.
Amazing
Kool place.   Would be good to bring family.   Mom and Dad can drink coffee and kids can paint pottery.  Slider sandwiches were very good.
Closed. For sale or lease sign.

I have been coming here since it opened back when I was in college and it has always been wonderful.  Such great quality for such a reasonable price, I have not found such a good deal anywhere else in town!  The fact that it has survived in an area where almost everything has changed, that in of itself tells you something!!
The combo's on the menu are great. The New Mexican sushi awesome! Very good place to get sushi! My new favorite spot! Going to go back to try more!

This place is awesome. I know one of the managers. The lady that owns the place is really cool. I have always enjoyed the food very much. It is for a fair price. It is also one of the only places I can find buckwheat noodles. I would highly recommend this to anybody who enjoys some good Asian food. Definitely some quality stuff here.

Sushi novice and our waiter was kind and patient,  even though it was Valentine's Day and they were very busy. 😳 Tried delicious and beautiful new types of sushi. If we're ever back in the area, we'll go back to Crazy Fish.
Really bomb food!! If you go for the lunch specials ($8-$10) the deals are amazing. I got a bento box combo with two entrees for $10 plus tip. Their sushi rolls are pretty thick. Going back for sure.

Instantly happy with the atmosphere as we entered and pleasantly greeted. Indoor/outdoor feel that was very comfortable. Menu was overloaded with selections! Service was good. Wait was long! My friends and I were pleased with the food. Portions were a bit off. Huge appetizers, but small sides. Baked potato was really firm. (Reheated maybe). Ribs were excellent. Scallops were perfect. Shrimp was good. Pasta was delicious. A little pricey, but overall a good experience. I'll go back to try some other things that I had to reluctantly pass on being my first time dining there.
Food was excellent,  service was great!  Laid back pace. Overall dining experience was well above average.

The food was so delish! Fresh Oysters...steak cooled to perfection...priced well for what you get.
Be sure to come hungry!

Overpriced! Salad is lettuce, one slice of tomato, one onion slice and one black olive. Ranch dressing was good.  Your drinks are in disposable plastic cups.  The meal was less than desirable.  The baked potato was not hot enough to melt the butter.  Green beans was served in a very small plastic disposable container.  My first and last time there.
Prime rib did not taste fresh baked? Baked potato small veg green beans in small container salad was warm old. 2. Bottled beers each and meal came to 70.00 for 2 people!!!!! Will not b back there.

11/03/13
We enjoyed eating here for the first time yesterday. We'd gotten hungry for barbecue and were reading the reviews and had been a little worried about what they said.
The wait staff here is very attentive! I know someone had said the portions here were small- I'd gotten the ribs and chicken combo and while the half slab on the plate *was* smaller than some I have seen, the platter was priced accordingly, as it was the same for ribs plus chicken here than I would just get a half slab and no chicken elsewhere. And after eating the meal, I felt comfortably full. I did see one could add another half slab to any meal for 6.99 which would be the price of a rib/chicken combo elsewhere, so surely with the extra half slab the portions are not small at all. My husband got the half chicken plate and it was more than he could eat, so the chicken is plenty, and also inexpensive as well.
The sides are good- the braised cabbage is done in an authentic southern style, seasoned up with meat. I also got the sweet potato which is served with cinnamon spread and you can get brown sugar and more cinnamon if you like. My husband got the baked beans which he remarked were excellent and also the collards, which although mild in taste, were punched right up with a splash of hot sauce.
I think the most important thing here is the genuine flavor of smoke--which being an avid barbecuer myself I can assure you that it tastes right. There is another place in town that I suspect pours liquid smoke in their brine and that flavor just overwhelms their meat, especially the chicken. Here the smoke tastes like it comes from the smoker and nowhere else.
We know we will be back, as this place does meet our standards. Our waitress told us that on Sundays the chicken is all-you-can-eat. I am looking forward to that and if I manage to have some room after dinner I will sample some of the pie. My husband tried a chiffon type pumpkin pie and it was marvelous!

Expensive for what you get. Pulled pork and ribs are alright, but I prefer City BBQ down the street. Since the pork and ribs are "alright" I would have liked the sauce to be better to cover for the meat, but the sauces are bland. The sides are O.K., nothing to really write home about. I stick with City BBQ for this neck of the woods (yes, there is MUCH better BBQ out there than City BBQ!)
I approve. I would have given five stars but I thought Famous Dave's had better ribs. One of the better BBQ joints in Dayton though for sure.
Great ribs and a fun staff. I would recommend over some local chains.
Best baby backs in Dayton, and cheap craft beer too!
